      "input_text": "detailed recursive learning for agentic workflow with agentmesh\ncontrolling multiple harneses",
      "output_text": "Here is a detailed summary of the concept of **Recursive Learning for an Agentic Workflow** using **AgentMesh** to control multiple **Harneses**.\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nThis concept describes a sophisticated, self-improving AI architecture where a central orchestrator (AgentMesh) manages a swarm of specialized agent instances (Harneses). The key innovation is **recursive learning**: the system not only executes tasks but also analyzes its own performance to automatically refine the instructions, tool configurations, and coordination strategies for future tasks. This creates a closed-loop feedback system that evolves its operational efficiency and problem-solving capabilities over time without direct human intervention.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Core Components\n\nThe system is built on three distinct layers:\n\n- **AgentMesh (The Orchestrator & Meta-Learner):**\n    - **Role:** The central intelligence. It is not just a router but a **recursive learning engine**.\n    - **Functions:**\n        - **Decomposition:** Breaks down high-level user goals into discrete, manageable sub-tasks.\n        - **Harnes Selection & Configuration:** Decides which Harnes (or combination thereof) is best suited for each ",
