      "output_text": "Here is a detailed summary of the latest trends in AI agents, based on the most recent developments (circa late 2024 and early 2025).\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nThe field of AI agents is undergoing a fundamental shift from simple, reactive chatbots to **autonomous, goal-oriented systems** capable of planning, using tools, and executing complex multi-step tasks. The focus has moved beyond pure language generation to **agency**\u2014the ability to perceive an environment, reason about it, and take action to achieve a specific objective. Key trends include the rise of agentic workflows, the maturation of tool use and function calling, the emergence of multi-agent systems, and a growing emphasis on safety, evaluation, and open-source development.\n\n---\n\n### 1. The Rise of Agentic Workflows and \"Agentic AI\"\n\nThis is the single most significant trend. Instead of a single prompt-response cycle, AI agents now operate in iterative loops:\n\n- **Planning & Decomposition:** An agent receives a high-level goal (e.g., \"Book a flight to London for a business trip next week\"). It then decomposes this into sub-tasks: check calendar, search for flights, compare prices, check visa requirements, book the best o",
