      "output_text": "Here is a detailed summary of the latest trends in AI agents, based on the most recent research and developments as of early 2025.\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nThe field of AI agents is undergoing a fundamental shift from simple, single-task chatbots to complex, autonomous, and collaborative systems. The core trend is the move from **reactive tools** to **proactive, goal-oriented entities** that can plan, reason, learn, and execute multi-step tasks with minimal human intervention. Key drivers include advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs), new architectural patterns like Multi-Agent Systems (MAS), and a focus on grounding agents in reality through tool use and memory.\n\n---\n\n### 1. The Rise of Autonomous Agentic Workflows\n\nThis is the single most dominant trend. Instead of a user prompting an AI for a single answer, agents are now designed to work towards a high-level goal over an extended period.\n\n- **Planning & Decomposition:** Agents can break down complex user requests (e.g., \"Plan a month-long trip to Japan\") into a series of sub-tasks (book flights, find hotels, create an itinerary, check visa requirements).\n- **Iterative Execution & Self-Reflection:** Agents don't just execu",
