      "input_text": "Research the latest trends in applied AI agent in pharmaceutical industry",
      "output_text": "Here is a detailed summary of the latest trends in applied AI agents within the pharmaceutical industry, based on the most recent developments (2024-2025).\n\n---\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nThe pharmaceutical industry is undergoing a paradigm shift from using AI as a passive analytical tool to deploying **autonomous and semi-autonomous AI agents**. These agents are not just predicting outcomes; they are taking actions, making decisions, and orchestrating complex workflows across the drug lifecycle. The core trend is the move from **generative AI (GenAI)** for content creation to **agentic AI** for task execution and process automation.\n\n### Key Trends in Applied AI Agents\n\n#### 1. Autonomous Drug Discovery & Design\nThe most high-impact trend is the use of AI agents to manage the iterative, multi-step process of early drug discovery.\n\n- **Molecular Design Agents:** Systems like **AlphaFold3-integrated agents** are now being combined with generative chemistry models. An AI agent can propose a novel molecule, predict its 3D structure, dock it virtually against a target protein, and then run a preliminary ADMET (Absorption, Distribution, Metabolism, Excretion, Toxicity) simulation\u2014all witho",
